ph is a curve that begins at the origin and moves horizontally to the right to the value t sub 1. It then moves downward and to the right and reaches a trough at a point about halfway between t sub 1 and t sub 2, and then moves upward and to the right until it reaches the horizontal axis at the value t sub 2. It then moves horizontally to the right until it ends.\" height=\"171\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR444854.g22.png\" width=\"370\"></div>"],"answer":0}]